    color = listColores.pop(0)
    return {
        'fillColor': color, 
        'color': 'black',
        'weight': 0.25,
        'fillOpacity': 0.3

In [98]:
def hippie(fm,era):
    salida = '''
    <h5>{fm}</h5>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td>{era}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <a href="https://rubensdmp.github.io/GeoUy/index.html">Visit our HTML tutorial</a>
    <div class="popup" onclick="myFunction()">Click me!
  <span class="popuptext" id="myPopup">Popup text...</span>
</div>
    '''.format(fm=fm,era=era)
    return salida

for unidad in listUnidades:
    if ud != unidad:
        color = np.random.randint(16, 256, size=3)
        color = [str(hex(i))[2:] for i in color]
        color = '#'+''.join(color).upper()
        ud = unidad

iframe = folium.IFrame(html,
                       width=100,
                       height=100)

popup = folium.Popup(iframe,
                     max_width=100)



for _, r in gdf.iterrows():
    # Without simplifying the representation of each borough,
    # the map might not be displayed
    sim_geo = gpd.GeoSeries(r['geometry'])
    geo_j = sim_geo.to_json()
    geo_j = folium.GeoJson(data=geo_j,
                        style_function=map_colors)
    folium.Popup(hippie(r['Unidad'],r['Era']),
                 sticky=False,parse_html=False,
                 width=1000,
                       height=100
                ).add_to(geo_j)
    geo_j.add_to(m)
